The food was okay and the portion sizes smaller than expected. We got the combo appetizers, beef pad thai, and massaman curry. They also gave us a free mango sticky rice since we ordered more than $30, even though we ordered through Uber and not their website. As a note, if you order on their website, they automatically add a 15% tip to your charge, even when choosing pick up.  The food was decent and some of them could have been better. The crispy pork wonton was basically just deep fried noodle, with barely any filling. The pad thai was too sweet and missing that signature sour flavor, not to mention too oily. The massaman curry was good with a lot of meat, though I wish they had given us more rice.  Overall, good but may not come again.

Quite the roller coaster of culinary emotions. I ordered two item larb with chicken,  penang curry with duck, and iced tea. The waitress brought both a glass and a carafe of tea.  Awesome! I never got the larb. The curry arrived and, for the first time in my dining out history,  it had Thai eggplant in it. The curry was nicely spicy, and prepared as I had requested. It was perfect,  until I tasted the first piece of duck. The duck was probably cooked last week, a bit too quickly in my opinion,  and kept in the cooler.  It was tough, dry, and the skin was inedible. I ate the vegetables and what I could of the meat. I always save my rice for last, to savor the curry. This was instant rice, not the jasmine rice I expected.  I didn't eat it. The bill was accurate. I left hungry,  and,  overall, disappointed.

We've chosen to have a lunch here after looking on the appealing pictures and reading mostly positive reviews on this site. What a big mistake it was! I wonder who and when placed all these pictures and wrote the reviews? We had their Kanom Jeeb dumplings, Green Curry and Drunken noodles and NONE of the dishes looked anywhere close to whats on the pictures and tasted even worth. Dumplings were store bought frozen Shaw Mai put for a few minutes in the microwave, Both noodle and curry had a very tough and chewy meat and curry was so watery you HAD to eat it with the spoon. We ordered medium spicy, they both didn't have spiciness at all. So the food was bad. The service was quick, rushed and unpleasant, kind of cafeteria type. And the value was poor considering the experience. Tip: if you don't what to loose even more money eating here do not order the tea (it will be tasteless and will cost you a fortune) No coming back and NO recommending to whose who know the REAL THAI taste.

I recently found this place by driving around aimlessly in Bethesda. This place has great, authentic Thai food for reasonable prices. Most of the menu has been Americanized, but if you know your favorite Thai foods by their actual names, you should be fine in ordering. The wait staff is very friendly and attentive and the place is decorated beautifully. For the vegetarians, there are many options for dinner!

We are big fans of Thai food and totally appreciate good Thai food without the fluff or in this case, an extra serving of coconut milk.  Which is why we were really happy to find our new local Thai favorite in Bethesda! The restaurant does seem to have some identity issue on if it is a restaurant or a pottery an antique store, but once you walk past the reception area, there is enough seating to be found. Service is good and to the point, if at times a tad bit sloppy. But the food makes up for it. Food was well cooked and flavorful. The spice level was to the liking of the wife and that is always good :) My rating of the dishes we ordered: Panang chicken - curry was yummy and chicken was tender and cooked well Pad Thai - decent portion size and well made Drunken Noodle with beef - the noodles and sauce were spot on but the beef was a tad bit chewy for my liking :( Shrimp Fried Rice - was very good too Chicken with Basil Leaves and Hot Chili Pepper - probably the weakest of the dishes that we ordered - the sauce had flavor but the chicken was dry and over cooked.  All in all, I would definitely recommend this place when in the area.
